node.text:
A recent video project I worked on with @protectningaloo 

It's been ten years since the Ningaloo Coast was inscribed on the World Heritage list. It’s now time to step up again and rally together for the future of Exmouth Gulf, Ningaloo’s Nursery. We need to ensure this remarkable area is kept free from industrialisation and protected for all time.

#protectningaloo #ningalooreef #coralbay #thisiswa#coralcoast #oceanphotography #underwaterphotography #ningaloo

node.title: Here’s to you Ningaloo: Celebrating 10 Years of World Heritage Listing

node.text:
A snippet of some footage I put together for @coralbayeco on the Ningaloo Reef. With multiple tours including whale shark tours, manta ray tours, a glass bottom boat and even humpback tours. The Ningaloo Reef is an ocean paradise!

Hope you enjoy! 🐢🐋🐠 

#whaleshark #turtle #coralbay #ningalooreef #catchyouincoralbay #coralcoast #ThisIsWA #SeeAustralia #underwater #snorkel #holidayherethisyear #ocean #dive #humpbackwhale

node.title: A day out with Coral Bay Ecotours

node.text:
Please watch and share this video by @mission_blue @robertoochoahe 
The Galapagos is under threat as more than 260 Chinese fishing ships are swarming the Galapágos Islands. They have been set up for the last three weeks in international waters just outside a 188-mile wide exclusive economic zone around the Galapagos Marine Reserve.
Many species targeted are endangered including whale sharks and hammerhead species.
An adult whale shark, nicknamed ‘Hope’ which was part of a satellite tracking program has stopped transmitting its location in the Galapagos area. It was last recorded near the area where the fleet was operating.
#galapagos #whaleshark #fishing #ecuador #missionblue @onlyone @sosgalapagos

node.text:
Last week @jakewiltonphoto and I were fortunate enough to visit the beautiful Kalbarri National Park on @australiascoralcoast.
Here is a short edit I put together of our day exploring. 

The park is over 186,000 hectares that includes the Murchison river gorge, ancient landscape and towering coastal cliffs. The park also includes the new Kalbarri Skywalk tourism precint sitting 100m above the Murchison River. 

Filming with @nikonaustralia
Music from @artlist
Thanks to @avisaustralia 

#kalbarrinationalpark #kalbarri #coralcoast #thisisWA #wanderoutyonder #explore #seeaustralia #australia #nikon #australiascoralcoast @westernaustralia @australia

node.text:
As our lives have changed momentarily, I made a short video to hopefully share some inspiration and positivity.

The footage was captured with the help of @samlawrencephoto on the Ningaloo Reef over the last few years. A place we have been lucky enough to call home. 
A big thanks also to @kotravellers and @jakewiltonphoto for contributing and helping with the video. 
Feel free to share this with your friends. 🙏💙 #stayinspired #staystrong #ocean #positivity #seeaustralia #whaleshark #turtle #ningalooreef #australiascoralcoast #justanotherdayinWA #travel #adventure #inspiration #freedive #underwater

node.text:
Capturing the stunning world of Raja Ampat with the @djiglobal Osmo Action. Raja Ampat is one of the most beautiful places I have ever seen above and below the surface. I loved using the @djiglobal Osmo Action whilst freediving and exploring the islands. The super slo-mo (240 fps) helped grab some stunning underwater captures and the rocksteady stabilization made for super smooth playback. The front-facing screen is also a unique feature that allows you to easily film yourself in action, at any moment.
@djiglobal @roam #seeyourselfinaction #osmoaction

node.title: DJI Osmo Action in Raja Ampat

node.text:
Floating in a field of jellies. 

Coinciding with the full moon and with a lot of luck, we randomly stumbled across this mass of jellyfish in the ocean. One of the magical moments of Raja Ampat. 

Freediver @ellemayell 

#freedive #ocean #diver #indtravel #wonderfulindonesia #nikonasia #underwater #nature #travel #marinelife #explore
